We want to visualise the frequency of superpower instance amoungst students

students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower))+
  geom_bar()

Customisation: colour Inside or outside the aes mapping The below will colour the bars

students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower))+
  geom_bar(fill = "light blue")

Customisation: colour Inside or outside the aes mapping The below will fill the bar blue and colour the outside red

students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower))+
  geom_bar(fill = "light blue",
           colour = "red")

Customisation: colour Inside or outside the aes mapping The below will change each bar into observations for each school year

students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower,
             fill = school_year))+
  geom_bar()

Position adjustments Instead of stacking the data vertically, dodge places them beside each other

students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower,
             fill = school_year)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge")

fill position gives each bar the same height and returns a proportion on a scale of 0-1

students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower,
             fill = school_year)) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill")

count_data <- students %>% 
  group_by(superpower, school_year) %>% 
  summarise(counts = n())
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'superpower'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
count_data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower,
             y = counts,
             fill = school_year)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity")

count_data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = superpower,
             y = counts,
             fill = school_year)) +
  geom_col()
